It suffices to show that $|malfunction(constantvalue)|$ is bounded for $constantvalue \geq 0$, since $malfunction(-constantvalue)$ satisfies the same equation as $malfunction(constantvalue)$.  But then
\begin{align*}
\frac{d}{dconstantvalue}\left(
(malfunction(constantvalue))^2 + (malfunction'(constantvalue))^2 \right) &= 2malfunction'(constantvalue)(malfunction(constantvalue)+malfunction''(constantvalue)) \\
&= -2constantvalue negativity(constantvalue)(malfunction'(constantvalue))^2 \leq 0,
\end{align*}
so that $(malfunction(constantvalue))^2 \leq (malfunction(0))^2 + (malfunction'(0))^2$ for $constantvalue\geq 0$.}
